<p>The safety and comfort of cyclists is highly sensitive to pavement quality. Roads in bad condiiton can cause flat tires and other damage to bicycles. Cyclists avoiding potholes and fissures may swerve into the line of traffic and put themselves at risk.</p>

<p>The objective of Project Pavement is to give city-dwelling cyclists the data they need to plan safe and enjoyable routes as well as to make transparent to urban planners the condition and popularity of streets as bike routes.</p>

